<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-912-466  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 912 466.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Nov 20 1989 v23 n47 p126(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Schmoozing with the dealers: talk to used equipment vendors tostay on top of the competitive market. (Marketplace) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Erbschloe, Michael.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Used computer equipment can keep information-system costs down forlarge and small organizations, but IS managers must develop goodrelationships with dealers to realize the benefits.andP;  IS managerscan postpone major purchases by buying used equipment on ashort-term basis until equipment offering better price/performanceis introduced.andP;  It is important to stay up on computer markets andto maintain contact with dealers: the used equipment marketgenerates much more competition between dealers, which createsgreater opportunities if good business relationships are nurturedwith dealers.andP;  National dealers often have a wide selection ofleased equipment, while local dealers can sometimes be moreresponsive, depending on what they may have in stock at themoment.andP;  Tips are provided on how to work with used equipmentdealers to get the best price on needed equipment.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Used EquipmentMISHardware SelectionEquipment AcquisitionPlanningTutorialManagement of EDP.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>